      "text": "Social media platforms such as Instagram, TikTok, and Snapchat have become an integral part of modern teenage life. According to recent surveys, teenagers spend an average of four to six hours per day on these platforms. This raises important questions about both the benefits and drawbacks of social media.\n\nOn the positive side, social media enables young people to stay connected with friends and family, particularly those who live far away. It also provides a space for creative expression, allowing users to share art, music, and writing with a global audience. Furthermore, social media can be a powerful tool for raising awareness about social issues, as seen in various youth-led movements.\n\nHowever, there are serious concerns about the negative effects. Research suggests that excessive use of social media is linked to increased levels of anxiety and depression, particularly among girls. The constant comparison with carefully edited images can damage self-esteem. Additionally, cyberbullying remains a significant problem, with many young people experiencing harassment online.\n\nPsychologists recommend finding a healthy balance. Setting time limits, taking regular breaks, and focusing on positive, meaningful interactions are all strategies that can help. The key is not to avoid social media entirely, but to use it mindfully.",
